comment: Jordan (LAC) hand checks Duncan (SAS) on his body while defending in the post.
Duncan (SAS) makes contact with Griffin's (LAC) arm just after the release and does not affect the layup attempt.
Jordan (LAC) cleanly blocks Duncan's (SAS) shot.
Mills (SAS) trips Paul (LAC) and causes him to fall to the floor.
Duncan (SAS) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Griffin (LAC) cleanly knocks the ball away from Belinelli (SAS).
Paul (LAC) makes contact with Mills' (SAS) arm and the contact affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Mills (SAS) backs into Barnes (LAC) and falls when Barnes moves out of the way to get to the rebound.
Duncan (SAS) cleanly knocks the ball away from Jordan (LAC).
Jordan (LAC) pushes Duncan (SAS) into Griffin (LAC) as he attempts the shot in the lane.
Prior to getting his hand on the ball, Leonard (SAS) makes contact with Griffin's (LAC) arm that affects his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
Duncan (SAS) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Duncan (SAS) cleanly strips the ball from Jordan (LAC).
Leonard (SAS) initiates the contact with Barnes (LAC) who maintains legal guarding position as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Mills (SAS) and Paul (LAC) make incidental contact on the perimeter.
Jordan (LAC) sets the screen on Mills (SAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Diaw (SAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Griffin's (LAC) drive to the basket.
Griffin (LAC) uses his off arm to knock away Diaw's (SAS) arm after he attempts the running shot in the lane.
Jordan (LAC) has his hand on Duncan's (SAS) hip, but does not push him or affect his shot attempt.
Green (SAS) and Griffin (LAC) briefly engage to establish post position.
Duncan's (SAS) contact with Paul (LAC) has no effect on his FOM.
Paul (LAC) commits a take foul on Mills (SAS).
Green (SAS) comes over the back and makes contact with Paul (LAC) that affects his ability to catch the inbounds pass.
Griffin (LAC) sets the screen on Leonard (SAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Crawford (LAC) and Leonard (SAS) briefly engage as Leonard attempts to get open during the inbounds play.
Jones (LAC) commits a take foul on Mills (SAS).
